<!--
XML: eXtensible Markup Language
   - Structure/Organization of data

API: Application Programming Interface
   - a modular interface of the system which is able to share
      data on the network

   - example: Money Deposit Interface of the Bank
       - Bank sells  "Merchant ID" to authorize
       - Usecase: E-Commerce Website basically 
   - Types:
       - Public API
       - Private API
       - Partner API (like - online payment on E-commerce from banking system) 
   - Architecture of an API
       - RESTfull (REST) API  {Uses JSON Document}
       - SOAP API {Uses XML Document}
       - RPC API (REMOTE PROCEDURE CALL)
            -RPC -XML
            -RPC - JSON       
-->
<person>
     <name id="10">Your Full Name</name>
     <email>email@domain.com</email>
     <phone>+977 9840051645</phone>
</person>
<!-- - XML uses User-Defined elements
     - where HTML uses pre-defined elements
     - XML is strict type language

     - To make valid XML 
       - DTD (Document Type Definition)
           - Internal & External
           - 'CDATA' and 'PCDATA' to use
       - XSD (XML Schema Definition)   
           - Data Type
           - Indicators (Order, Group, Occurence(min, max))
           - Element types in XML (SimpleType or ComplexType)
           - Facets (Constraints)
           - Pattern (REGEX)
       - XSL(T)
         (XML StyleSheet language - Transformation)
          - To convert one structure to another
              - XML to HTML
              - XML to XML etc
       - XQuery (XML Query)
           - Like SQL Query
           - XQuery uses 'XPath'. example: person/name/@id
           - As SQL has standard SELECT Query statement
           XQuery has: FLOWR
                       F - For
                       L - Let
                       0 - Order
                       W - Where
                       R - Return   
               - Tool to work with XQuery: BaseX

To write XML and check in standard way:
    - Tool: XML Copy Editor  

XML should be:
    1st: Well Formed
    2nd: Valid                           
 -->